main event: Two unidentified flying objects were observed north of Macon, Georgia on March 26, 1966.
interesting points: One object was ball-shaped and the other was about the size of a dime at arm's length.
The objects were traveling in separate directions, with one moving from east to south and the other from south to north.
The first object was visible for about 4 minutes, and the second object was visible for about 10 minutes.
The investigator concluded that the objects were likely commercial aircraft that were seen from the ground.
No physical evidence or photographs were available.
